eu.slipo.athenarc.triplegeo.utils

Class RMLConverter

  • java.lang.Object
    • eu.slipo.athenarc.triplegeo.utils.RMLConverter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Converter

    public class RMLConverter
extends java.lang.Object
implements Converter
    Creates and populates a RML dataset so that data can be serialized into a file. LIMITATIONS: - No support for dynamically executed built-in functions (e.g., for calculating on-the-fly the area or length of geometries). - By convention, attribute names referring to input data must be specified in UPPER-CASE letters in the RML mappings (in .TTL files). - Currently, no support for transformation from OSM or GPX or on top of Spark.
    Version:
    2.0
    Author:
    Kostas Patroumpas

        classific - Instantiation of the classification scheme that assigns categories to input features.
        reproject - CRS transformation parameters to be used in reprojecting a geometry to a target SRID (EPSG code).
        targetSRID - Spatial reference system (EPSG code) of geometries in the output RDF triples.
        outputFile - Path to the output file that collects RDF triples.
